\\caption{(a) A binary search tree with keys 2, 3, 4, 7, 8, 10. (b) The persistent binary search tree that results from the insertion of key 5. The most recent version of the set consists of the nodes reachable from the root $r'$, and the previous version consists of the nodes reachable from $r$. Heavily shaded nodes are added when key 5 is inserted.}
