attribute of each node on the path. Since this path has length $O(\\lg n)$ in an $n$-node red-black tree, the additional time spent maintaining \\textit{size} attributes in the first phase is $O(\\lg n)$. We handle the $O(1)$ rotations in the second phase of deletion in the same manner as for insertion. Thus, both insertion and deletion, including maintaining the \\textit{size} attributes, take $O(\\lg n)$ time for an $n$-node order-statistic tree.

