\\subsection*{26-2 Minimum path cover}

A \\textbf{path cover} of a directed graph $G = (V, E)$ is a set $P$ of vertex-disjoint paths such that every vertex in $V$ is included in exactly one path in $P$. Paths may start and end anywhere, and they may be of any length, including 0. A \\textbf{minimum path cover} of $G$ is a path cover containing the fewest possible paths.

\\textbf{a.} Give an efficient algorithm to find a minimum path cover of a directed acyclic graph $G = (V, E)$. (Hint: Assuming that $V = \\{1, 2, \\dots, n\\}$, construct the graph $G' = (V', E')$, where
\\begin{align*}
V' &= \\{x_0, x_1, \\dots, x_n\\} \\cup \\{y_0, y_1, \\dots, y_n\\}, \\\\
E' &= \\{(x_0, x_i) : i \\in V\\} \\cup \\{(y_i, y_0) : i \\in V\\} \\cup \\{(x_i, y_j) : (i, j) \\in E\\},
\\end{align*}
and run a maximum-flow algorithm.)

